Ingredients: 1 medium head cauliflower, cut into florets. � cup whole wheat flour. � cup water. � cup low-sodium hot sauce. 1 teaspoon garlic powder. 1 tablespoon olive oil. � teaspoon salt
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 425�F (220�C). 2. In a bowl, whisk together the flour, water, garlic powder, and salt until smooth. 3. Dip each cauliflower floret into the batter and place them on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. 4. Bake for 20 minutes until tender and slightly crispy. 5. In a separate bowl, mix the hot sauce and olive oil. Toss the baked cauliflower in the sauce until well coated. 6. Return to the oven and bake for another 10 minutes. Serve hot.

Description: A fresh salad that combines tender chicken, crunchy veggies, and a zesty dressing, making it a satisfying meal option.
Ingredients: 2 cups cooked chicken breast, shredded. 4 cups mixed greens. � cup cherry tomatoes, halved. � cup low-sodium hot sauce. 2 tablespoons olive oil. 1 tablespoon apple cider vinegar. � teaspoon black pepper.
Instructions: 1. In a large bowl, combine the mixed greens, cherry tomatoes, and shredded chicken. 2. In a small bowl, whisk together the hot sauce, olive oil, apple cider vinegar, and black pepper. 3. Pour the dressing over the salad and toss gently to combine. 4. Serve immediately, or refrigerate for up to 30 minutes before serving.

Description: A delicious and easy-to-make wrap that's perfect for lunch or a quick dinner on the go, filled with tender chicken and veggies.
Ingredients: 1 whole wheat tortilla. 1 cup cooked chicken breast, shredded. � cup low-sodium hot sauce. � cup lettuce, shredded. � cup cucumber, sliced. 2 tablespoons low-sodium ranch dressing.
Instructions: 1. In a bowl, mix the shredded chicken with hot sauce. 2. Lay the tortilla flat and add the lettuce, cucumber, and chicken mixture. 3. Drizzle ranch dressing on top, then roll the tortilla tightly. 4. Slice in half and serve immediately or wrap in foil for later.

Description: A delicious low-carb twist on traditional Bulgogi served over cauliflower rice for a healthy and renal-friendly dinner.
Ingredients: 1 lb lean beef, thinly sliced. 2 tablespoons soy sauce (low sodium). 1 tablespoon sesame oil. 1 tablespoon brown sugar substitute. 2 garlic cloves, minced. 1 teaspoon grated ginger. 1 cup cauliflower rice. 1 green onion, chopped. 1 carrot, julienned. 1 tablespoon sesame seeds
Instructions: 1. In a bowl, combine soy sauce, sesame oil, brown sugar substitute, garlic, and ginger. Add the beef slices and marinate for at least 30 minutes. 2. In a skillet over medium heat, cook the marinated beef until browned, about 5-7 minutes. Remove and set aside. 3. In the same skillet, add cauliflower rice and cook until it's tender. 4. Add the cooked beef back to the skillet along with the carrot, mixing well until everything is heated through. 5. Serve the Bulgogi over the cauliflower rice, garnished with green onions and sesame seeds.

Description: Flavorful marinated beef served in crisp lettuce leaves for a fresh and healthy snack or appetizer.
Ingredients: 1 lb lean ground beef. 2 tablespoons low-sodium soy sauce. 1 tablespoon sesame oil. 1 tablespoon sugar substitute. 2 garlic cloves, minced. 1 teaspoon grated ginger. 8 large lettuce leaves. 1 carrot, shredded. 1 cucumber, thinly sliced
Instructions: 1. In a bowl, mix together the soy sauce, sesame oil, sugar substitute, garlic, and ginger. Add the ground beef and mix well. 2. Cook the beef mixture in a skillet over medium heat until browned and cooked through. 3. Lay out the lettuce leaves and fill them with the beef mixture. 4. Top with shredded carrot and cucumber slices. 5. Serve immediately for a crunchy, fresh experience.

Description: A nourishing bowl of quinoa topped with succulent Bulgogi and fresh vegetables, perfect for lunch or dinner.
Ingredients: 1 cup cooked quinoa. 1 lb beef, thinly sliced. 2 tablespoons low-sodium soy sauce. 1 tablespoon sesame oil. 1 tablespoon brown sugar substitute. 1 cup mixed salad greens. � cup bell peppers, sliced. � avocado, sliced
Instructions: 1. Marinate the beef in soy sauce, sesame oil, and brown sugar substitute for at least 30 minutes. 2. Cook the beef in a skillet until browned. 3. In a bowl, layer quinoa, cooked beef, salad greens, bell peppers, and avocado. 4. Drizzle with additional soy sauce if desired. 5. Toss and serve warm.

Description: Colorful bell peppers stuffed with savory Bulgogi and vegetables for a nutritious and eye-catching dinner.
Ingredients: 4 bell peppers (any color). 1 lb beef, thinly sliced. 2 tablespoons low-sodium soy sauce. 1 tablespoon sesame oil. 1 tablespoon sugar substitute. 1 cup sliced mushrooms. 1 small onion, diced
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 375�F (190�C). 2. Saut� onions and mushrooms in a skillet until soft, then add the beef and cook until browned. Stir in soy sauce, sesame oil, and sugar substitute. 3. Cut the tops off the bell peppers and remove seeds. 4. Stuff each pepper with the Bulgogi mixture and place in a baking dish. 5. Bake for 25-30 minutes until peppers are tender.

Description: Spiraled zucchini noodles topped with flavorful Bulgogi, perfect for a light and healthy meal.
Ingredients: 2 medium zucchinis, spiraled. 1 lb lean beef, thinly sliced. 2 tablespoons low-sodium soy sauce. 1 tablespoon sesame oil. 1 tablespoon brown sugar substitute. 2 garlic cloves, minced. 1 tablespoon chopped green onions
Instructions: 1. Marinate the beef with soy sauce, sesame oil, brown sugar substitute, and garlic for at least 30 minutes. 2. Cook the beef in a skillet until browned. 3. In the same skillet, add zucchini noodles and saut� for 2-3 minutes until just tender. 4. Add the cooked beef to the zucchini noodles and toss to combine. 5. Garnish with chopped green onions and serve immediately.

Description: A hearty and healthy burger made from black beans and vegetables, perfect for a satisfying meal.
Ingredients: 1 can (15 oz) black beans, rinsed and drained. 1/2 cup breadcrumbs, whole wheat. 1/2 cup corn, canned or frozen. 1/4 cup red onion, finely chopped. 1/4 cup bell pepper, finely chopped. 1 clove garlic, minced. 1 tablespoon olive oil. 1 teaspoon cumin powder. Salt and pepper to taste.
Instructions: 1. Preheat your oven to 375�F (190�C). 2. In a mixing bowl, mash the black beans with a fork. 3. Stir in the breadcrumbs, corn, red onion, bell pepper, garlic, olive oil, cumin, salt, and pepper until well combined. 4. Form the mixture into patties. 5. Place the patties on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. 6. Bake for 20-25 minutes, flipping halfway through, until golden and firm. 7. Serve on whole-grain buns with your choice of lettuce, tomato, and sauces.

Description: A lean and protein-packed turkey burger flavored with spices, great for a nutritious dinner.
Ingredients: 1 lb ground turkey. 1/4 cup breadcrumbs, whole wheat. 1/4 cup onion, finely chopped. 1 egg, beaten. 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce. 1 teaspoon garlic powder. Salt and pepper to taste.
Instructions: 1. In a bowl, combine ground turkey, breadcrumbs, onion, egg, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, salt, and pepper. 2. Mix until just combined, being careful not to overmix. 3. Form into 4 burger patties. 4. Preheat a skillet over medium heat, lightly grease it. 5. Cook patties for 5-6 minutes on each side until cooked through and internal temperature reaches 165�F (74�C). 6. Serve on whole-grain buns with toppings of choice.

Description: A delightful chickpea patty packed with flavor and nutrients, perfect for a veggie lover.
Ingredients: 1 can (15 oz) chickpeas, rinsed and drained. 1/2 cup oatmeal, ground. 1/4 cup onion, finely chopped. 1/4 cup carrot, grated. 1 tablespoon olive oil. 1 teaspoon cumin. Salt and pepper to taste.
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 375�F (190�C). 2. In a bowl, mash the chickpeas with a fork or potato masher. 3. Add ground oatmeal, onion, carrot, olive oil, cumin, salt, and pepper. Mix until combined. 4. Form into patties and place on a baking sheet. 5. Bake for 25-30 minutes, flipping halfway through, until golden. 6. Serve on whole-grain buns with desired toppings.

Description: A protein-rich lentil burger that provides a satisfying and tasty option for any meal.
Ingredients: 1 cup cooked lentils. 1/2 cup breadcrumbs, whole wheat. 1/4 cup onion, minced. 1 carrot, grated. 1 clove garlic, minced. 1 tablespoon soy sauce. 1 tablespoon olive oil. Salt and pepper to taste.
Instructions: 1. In a bowl, mash the cooked lentils. 2. Add breadcrumbs, onion, carrot, garlic, soy sauce, olive oil, salt, and pepper. Mix well. 3. Form into patties. 4. Heat a skillet over medium heat with a little olive oil. 5. Cook patties for 5-7 minutes on each side until they are browned and heated through. 6. Serve on whole-grain buns with preferred toppings.

Description: A nutritious burger with quinoa and vegetables for added texture and flavor.
Ingredients: 1/2 cup cooked quinoa. 1 can (15 oz) black beans, rinsed and drained. 1/4 cup red bell pepper, finely chopped. 1/4 cup onion, finely chopped. 1 tablespoon olive oil. 1 tablespoon ground flaxseed. Salt and pepper to taste.
Instructions: 1. In a bowl, combine cooked quinoa, black beans, bell pepper, onion, olive oil, flaxseed, salt, and pepper. 2. Mash the mixture until well blended. 3. Form into 4 patties. 4. Preheat a skillet over medium-high heat, adding a bit of olive oil. 5. Cook patties for 4-5 minutes on each side or until browned. 6. Serve on whole-grain buns with your favorite toppings.

Recipe Name: Burrito with Black Beans and Brown Rice
Description: A hearty burrito filled with black beans and brown rice, perfect for a healthy meal.
Ingredients: 1 whole wheat tortilla, 1 cup cooked brown rice, � cup canned black beans, rinsed and drained, � cup diced tomatoes, � cup diced bell pepper, � cup corn, 1 tablespoon olive oil, 1 teaspoon cumin, 1 tablespoon lime juice, Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions: 1. Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat. 2. Add bell pepper and saut� until softened, about 5 minutes. 3. Stir in black beans, corn, tomatoes, cumin, lime juice, salt, and pepper. Cook until heated through. 4. Lay the tortilla flat and add the brown rice and bean mixture. Fold the sides in and roll tightly. 5. Serve with a side of salsa if desired.

Description: A nutritious burrito loaded with quinoa and fresh vegetables, ideal for those seeking a light and healthy option.
Ingredients: 1 whole wheat tortilla, � cup cooked quinoa, � cup mixed vegetables (zucchini, bell peppers, carrots), 1 tablespoon olive oil, 1 teaspoon garlic powder, 1 tablespoon cilantro, Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions: 1. In a skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat. 2. Add mixed vegetables and saut� until soft. 3. Stir in quinoa, garlic powder, salt, pepper, and cilantro. Cook for another 2-3 minutes. 4. Place the mixture on a tortilla, fold in the sides, and roll tightly. 5. Serve with your favorite hot sauce.

Description: A protein-rich burrito made with lentils and spinach, providing a filling and healthy meal option.
Ingredients: 1 whole wheat tortilla, 1 cup cooked lentils, 1 cup fresh spinach, � cup diced onions, 1 tablespoon olive oil, 1 teaspoon paprika, Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions: 1. Heat olive oil in a pan and saut� onions until translucent. 2. Stir in the cooked lentils and spinach, cook until spinach is wilted. 3. Season with paprika, salt, and pepper. 4. Spoon the mixture onto a tortilla, fold, and roll into a burrito. 5. Slice in half and serve warm.

Description: A creamy and satisfying burrito filled with chickpeas and avocado, perfect for a nutritious snack or meal.
Ingredients: 1 whole wheat tortilla, � cup canned chickpeas, rinsed and drained, � avocado, mashed, � cup diced tomatoes, 1 tablespoon lime juice, Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions: 1. In a bowl, mash the avocado and combine with chickpeas, diced tomatoes, lime juice, salt, and pepper. 2. Spread the mixture onto a tortilla. 3. Roll tightly to form a burrito. 4. Serve fresh with additional lime wedges if desired.

Description: A spicy burrito packed with marinated tofu and fresh salsa, offering a burst of flavor in every bite.
Ingredients: 1 whole wheat tortilla, � cup firm tofu, cubed, � cup salsa, � cup diced bell pepper, 1 tablespoon olive oil, 1 teaspoon chili powder, Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions: 1. Toss cubed tofu with olive oil, chili powder, salt, and pepper. 2. Bake or pan-fry until golden. 3. Mix the cooked tofu with salsa and bell pepper. 4. Place the mixture in a tortilla, fold, and roll tightly. 5. Serve warm.

Description: A creamy, comforting soup that showcases the natural sweetness of butternut squash, enhanced with fresh thyme.
Ingredients: 2 cups butternut squash, peeled and cubed. 1 medium onion, chopped. 2 cloves garlic, minced. 4 cups vegetable broth. 1 tablespoon olive oil. 1 teaspoon fresh thyme. Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions: 1. In a large pot, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add the chopped onion and garlic, saut� until soft. 2. Add the cubed butternut squash and stir for a few minutes. 3. Pour in the vegetable broth and add thyme, salt, and pepper. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for about 20 minutes until the squash is tender. 4. Use an immersion blender to puree the soup until smooth. 5. Serve warm, garnished with a sprig of thyme if desired.

Recipe Name: Creamy Butternut Squash and Coconut Soup
Description: A luscious blend of butternut squash and coconut milk for a tropical twist on a classic soup.
Ingredients: 3 cups butternut squash, peeled and diced. 1 can (14 oz) coconut milk. 1 medium onion, diced. 2 cups vegetable broth. 1 tablespoon olive oil. 1 teaspoon curry powder. Salt to taste
Instructions: 1. Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add onion and saut� until translucent. 2. Add diced butternut squash and curry powder, stirring for a couple of minutes. 3. Pour in vegetable broth and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until squash is soft, about 20 minutes. 4. Stir in coconut milk, then puree with an immersion blender or in batches in a regular blender. 5. Adjust seasoning if necessary and serve hot.

Recipe Name: Spiced Butternut Squash Soup with Ginger
Description: This warming soup is enhanced with the zesty flavor of ginger, perfect for a chilly day.
Ingredients: 2 cups butternut squash, peeled and diced. 1 tablespoon fresh ginger, grated. 1 medium onion, chopped. 4 cups vegetable broth. 1 tablespoon olive oil. 1 teaspoon cumin. Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions: 1. In a pot, heat olive oil over medium heat and saut� the onion until soft. 2. Add grated ginger and cumin, and stir for a minute. 3. Incorporate the butternut squash, followed by vegetable broth. Bring to a boil. 4. Lower the heat, cover, and simmer for 20 minutes until the squash is tender. 5. Puree with an immersion blender, season with salt and pepper, and serve.

Description: A hearty and nutritious soup that combines butternut squash with protein-rich lentils for a satisfying meal.
Ingredients: 2 cups butternut squash, diced. 1 cup cooked lentils. 1 medium onion, chopped. 4 cups vegetable broth. 1 tablespoon olive oil. 1 teaspoon smoked paprika. Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions: 1. In a large pot, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add onion and cook until soft. 2. Stir in the butternut squash and smoked paprika, cooking for a few minutes. 3. Add cooked lentils and vegetable broth, bring to a boil. 4. Reduce heat and simmer for about 20 minutes until the squash is soft. 5. Blend until smooth if desired, season with salt and pepper, and serve warm.

Recipe Name: Cabbage Rolls with Quinoa and Vegetables
Description: A wholesome dish that incorporates cabbage leaves filled with a savory mixture of quinoa, vegetables, and spices, ideal for a renal diet.
Ingredients: 1 head green cabbage, 1 cup quinoa, uncooked, 2 cups vegetable broth, 1 cup chopped tomatoes (canned), 1 medium onion, finely chopped, 1 medium carrot, grated, 1 teaspoon garlic powder, 1 teaspoon dried oregano, Salt and pepper to taste, 1 tablespoon olive oil
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 375�F (190�C). 2. Boil the cabbage in a large pot of water for about 5 minutes until leaves are softened. Remove and let cool. 3. In a medium pot, combine quinoa and vegetable broth. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat, cover, and simmer for 15 minutes. 4. In a large bowl, mix cooked quinoa, chopped tomatoes, onion, carrot, garlic powder, oregano, salt, and pepper. 5. Take a cabbage leaf, fill it with quinoa mixture, and roll tightly. Place in a baking dish. 6. Drizzle olive oil over the rolls and cover with foil. Bake for 30 minutes. Serve warm.

Recipe Name: Cabbage Rolls with Lean Ground Turkey
Description: Cabbage rolls filled with lean ground turkey and rice create a satisfying meal that�s hearty yet light.
Ingredients: 1 head green cabbage, 1 pound lean ground turkey, 1 cup brown rice, uncooked, 2 cups low-sodium chicken broth, 1 can (15 oz) diced tomatoes, 1 medium onion, finely chopped, 1 teaspoon garlic powder, 1 teaspoon dried thyme, Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions: 1. Preheat oven to 350�F (175�C). 2. Boil cabbage for 5 minutes to soften leaves and cool. 3. Cook brown rice in chicken broth according to package instructions. 4. In a mixing bowl, combine cooked rice, turkey, tomatoes, onion, garlic powder, thyme, salt, and pepper. 5. Roll the mixture in cabbage leaves and place in a baking dish. 6. Cover with foil and bake for 40 minutes. Serve with tomato sauce if desired.

Description: A hearty, vegetarian option filled with zucchini, mushrooms, and rice, providing essential nutrients without the need for meat.
Ingredients: 1 head green cabbage, 1 cup brown rice, uncooked, 1 cup chopped zucchini, 1 cup chopped mushrooms, 1 cup diced bell peppers, 1 teaspoon garlic powder, 1 teaspoon dried basil, Salt and pepper to taste, 1 can (15 oz) diced tomatoes
Instructions: 1. Preheat oven to 350�F (175�C). 2. Boil cabbage for 5 minutes to pliable leaves and let cool. 3. Cook brown rice according to package directions. 4. In a bowl, mix cooked rice with zucchini, mushrooms, bell peppers, garlic powder, basil, salt, and pepper. 5. Fill cabbage leaves with vegetable mixture and roll tightly. Place in a baking dish and cover with diced tomatoes. 6. Bake for 30 minutes until heated through. Serve hot.

Description: Nutritious lentils and rice rolled in cabbage leaves make a filling yet healthy dish, suitable for a renal diet.
Ingredients: 1 head green cabbage, 1 cup lentils, rinsed, 1 cup white rice, uncooked, 3 cups vegetable broth, 1 medium onion, finely chopped, 1 teaspoon cumin, Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions: 1. Preheat oven to 375�F (190�C). 2. Boil the cabbage for about 5 minutes or until leaves soften. 3. Cook lentils and rice in vegetable broth until done (about 20 minutes for lentils and 15 minutes for rice). 4. In a bowl, mix cooked lentils, rice, onion, cumin, salt, and pepper. 5. Fill cabbage leaves with the lentil mixture and roll them up. Place in a baking dish. 6. Bake covered with foil for 25 minutes. Serve warm.

Recipe Name: Cabbage Rolls with Brown Rice and Peas
Description: A delightful mix of brown rice and peas rolled into cabbage leaves for a nutritious meal perfect for any time.
Ingredients: 1 head green cabbage, 1 cup brown rice, uncooked, 1 cup frozen peas, 1 medium onion, finely chopped, 1 teaspoon thyme, Salt and pepper to taste, 1 can (15 oz) diced tomatoes
Instructions: 1. Preheat oven to 350�F (175�C). 2. Boil the cabbage for 5 minutes to soften leaves. 3. Cook brown rice according to package directions. 4. In a bowl, combine cooked rice, peas, onion, thyme, salt, and pepper. 5. Fill cabbage leaves with the rice mixture and roll up tightly. Place rolls in a baking dish and top with diced tomatoes. 6. Bake for 30 minutes until heated through. Serve hot.

Description: A moist and delicious cake made with almond flour, perfect for a gluten-free dessert option.
Ingredients: 2 cups almond flour, � cup unsweetened cocoa powder, � cup erythritol or sugar substitute, 4 large eggs, � cup unsweetened applesauce, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract, 1 teaspoon baking soda, � teaspoon salt, � cup unsweetened almond milk
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 350�F (175�C). Grease a 9-inch round cake pan. 2. In a large bowl, mix almond flour, cocoa powder, erythritol, baking soda, and salt. 3. In another bowl, whisk eggs, applesauce, and vanilla extract until smooth. 4. Combine the wet ingredients with the dry ingredients and mix until well incorporated. 5. Slowly add almond milk until the batter reaches a smooth consistency. 6. Pour batter into the prepared pan and bake for 25-30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean. 7. Let it cool before serving.

Description: A flavorful cake made with grated carrots and shredded coconut, great for a sweet treat.
Ingredients: 1 � cups whole wheat flour, 1 cup grated carrots, � cup shredded unsweetened coconut, � cup erythritol or sugar substitute, 4 large eggs, � cup unsweetened almond milk, 1 teaspoon baking powder, � teaspoon cinnamon, � teaspoon salt
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 350�F (175�C). Grease a 9-inch round cake pan. 2. In a large bowl, mix flour, erythritol, baking powder, cinnamon, and salt. 3. In another bowl, whisk eggs and almond milk until well combined. 4. Stir in grated carrots and shredded coconut. 5. Combine the wet ingredients with the dry ingredients and mix until smooth. 6. Pour the batter into the prepared pan and bake for 30-35 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. 7. Allow the cake to cool before serving.

Description: A moist pumpkin cake with warm spices, perfect for enjoying a slice during the fall.
Ingredients: 1 � cups whole wheat flour, 1 cup canned pumpkin puree, � cup erythritol or sugar substitute, 4 large eggs, � cup unsweetened almond milk, 1 teaspoon baking soda, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, � teaspoon nutmeg, � teaspoon salt
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 350�F (175�C). Grease a 9-inch round cake pan. 2. In a bowl, combine whole wheat flour, erythritol, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt. 3. In another bowl, whisk together eggs, almond milk, and pumpkin puree until smooth. 4. Mix the wet ingredients with the dry ingredients until well combined. 5. Pour the batter into the prepared pan and bake for 30-35 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. 6. Cool before serving.

Description: A deliciously moist cake with grated zucchini and chocolate chips, great for a dessert or a snack.
Ingredients: 1 � cups whole wheat flour, 1 cup grated zucchini, � cup erythritol or sugar substitute, 4 large eggs, � cup unsweetened almond milk, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract, 1 teaspoon baking powder, 1 cup sugar-free chocolate chips, � teaspoon salt
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 350�F (175�C). Grease a 9-inch round cake pan. 2. In a bowl, combine flour, erythritol, baking powder, and salt. 3. In another bowl, whisk eggs, almond milk, and vanilla extract until combined. 4. Stir in grated zucchini and then add the dry ingredients. 5. Fold in chocolate chips. 6. Pour into the prepared pan and bake for 30-35 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. 7. Cool before serving.

Description: A deliciously stuffed calzone filled with creamy ricotta cheese and fresh spinach, perfect for a savory meal.
Ingredients: 1 cup whole wheat flour, � cup warm water, 1 teaspoon olive oil, 1 teaspoon sugar, � teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon active dry yeast, 1 cup ricotta cheese, 2 cups fresh spinach, � cup shredded mozzarella cheese, � teaspoon black pepper, � teaspoon garlic powder
Instructions: 1. In a bowl, mix warm water, sugar, and yeast. Let sit for 5 minutes until frothy. 2. Combine flour and salt in a large mixing bowl. Add the yeast mixture and olive oil. Knead until smooth. 3. Cover and let rise for 1 hour. 4. Saut� spinach until wilted, mix in ricotta, mozzarella, black pepper, and garlic powder. 5. Preheat oven to 400�F (200�C). Roll out dough, fill with spinach mixture, and fold. Seal edges. 6. Bake for 20-25 minutes until golden brown.

Description: A protein-packed calzone with chicken and colorful vegetables, making it perfect for a filling lunch or dinner.
Ingredients: 1 cup whole wheat flour, � cup warm water, 1 teaspoon olive oil, 1 teaspoon sugar, � teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon active dry yeast, 1 cup cooked chicken, diced, � cup bell peppers, diced, � cup zucchini, diced, � cup onion, diced, � teaspoon oregano, � teaspoon black pepper
Instructions: 1. In a bowl, mix warm water, sugar, and yeast. Let sit for 5 minutes until frothy. 2. Mix flour and salt in a large bowl, then add the yeast mixture and oil. Knead until smooth. 3. Cover and let rise for 1 hour. 4. Saut� bell peppers, zucchini, and onion until tender. Add cooked chicken, oregano, and black pepper. 5. Preheat oven to 400�F (200�C). Roll out dough, fill with the chicken mixture, and fold. Seal edges. 6. Bake for 20-25 minutes until golden.

Description: A delightful twist on the classic caprese salad, packed into a calzone for an easy and tasty meal.
Ingredients: 1 cup whole wheat flour, � cup warm water, 1 teaspoon olive oil, 1 teaspoon sugar, � teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon active dry yeast, 1 cup fresh mozzarella, diced, 1 medium tomato, diced, � cup fresh basil, chopped, 1 tablespoon balsamic glaze
Instructions: 1. In a bowl, mix warm water, sugar, and yeast. Let sit for 5 minutes until frothy. 2. Combine flour and salt in a large bowl, then add the yeast mixture and olive oil. Knead until smooth. 3. Cover and let rise for 1 hour. 4. In a bowl, mix mozzarella, tomato, basil, and balsamic glaze. 5. Preheat oven to 400�F (200�C). Roll out dough, fill with the mixture, and fold. Seal edges. 6. Bake for 20-25 minutes until golden.

Description: A savory calzone filled with caramelized mushrooms and onions for a hearty, vegetarian dish.
Ingredients: 1 cup whole wheat flour, � cup warm water, 1 teaspoon olive oil, 1 teaspoon sugar, � teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon active dry yeast, 1 cup mushrooms, sliced, � cup onion, sliced, � cup shredded mozzarella cheese, � teaspoon thyme, � teaspoon black pepper
Instructions: 1. In a bowl, combine warm water, sugar, and yeast. Let sit for 5 minutes until frothy. 2. Mix flour and salt in a large bowl. Add the yeast mixture and olive oil. Knead until smooth. 3. Cover and let rise for 1 hour. 4. Saut� mushrooms and onions until caramelized. Add thyme and pepper. 5. Preheat oven to 400�F (200�C). Roll out dough, load with the mushroom mixture, and fold. Seal edges. 6. Bake for 20-25 minutes until golden.

Recipe Name: Veggie Calzone with Bell Peppers and Broccoli
Description: A colorful calzone loaded with nutritious bell peppers and broccoli, perfect for a wholesome meal.
Ingredients: 1 cup whole wheat flour, � cup warm water, 1 teaspoon olive oil, 1 teaspoon sugar, � teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon active dry yeast, 1 cup bell peppers, diced, 1 cup broccoli florets, steamed, � cup ricotta cheese, � teaspoon black pepper
Instructions: 1. In a bowl, combine warm water, sugar, and yeast. Let sit for 5 minutes until frothy. 2. Combine flour and salt in a large bowl. Add the yeast mixture and olive oil. Knead until smooth. 3. Cover and let rise for 1 hour. 4. In a bowl, mix bell peppers, broccoli, ricotta, and black pepper. 5. Preheat oven to 400�F (200�C). Roll out dough, fill with the veggie mixture, and fold. Seal edges. 6. Bake for 20-25 minutes until golden.

Description: Moist, flavorful muffins made with fresh carrots and a hint of cinnamon, perfect for breakfast or a snack.
Ingredients: 1 � cups whole wheat flour, 1 teaspoon baking powder, 1 teaspoon baking soda, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, � teaspoon nutmeg, 1 cup grated carrots, � cup unsweetened applesauce, � cup honey, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract, � cup chopped walnuts (optional)
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 350�F (175�C). Line a muffin tin with paper liners. 2. In a mixing bowl, combine whole wheat flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, and nutmeg. 3. In another bowl, mix grated carrots, applesauce, honey, and vanilla extract. 4. Combine the wet and dry ingredients, and fold in walnuts if using. 5. Fill muffin cups about � full and bake for 18-20 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean. Let cool before serving.

Description: A lighter take on a classic dessert, made with whole ingredients and spiced with warming cinnamon and ginger.
Ingredients: 1 � cups whole wheat flour, 1 teaspoon baking powder, � teaspoon baking soda, 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon, � teaspoon ground ginger, 1 cup grated carrots, � cup unsweetened applesauce, � cup maple syrup, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract, � cup crushed pineapple, drained
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 350�F (175�C) and grease an 8-inch round cake pan. 2. In a mixing bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, and ginger. 3. In a separate bowl, mix grated carrots, applesauce, maple syrup, vanilla extract, and crushed pineapple. 4. Combine wet and dry ingredients until just mixed. 5. Pour batter into prepared pan and bake for 25-30 minutes. Cool before serving.

Description: No-bake bites packed with the flavors of carrot cake, great for a quick energizing snack.
Ingredients: 1 cup rolled oats, � cup grated carrots, � cup almond butter, � cup honey, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, � teaspoon nutmeg, � cup chopped walnuts
Instructions: 1. In a bowl, combine all ingredients and mix until well combined. 2. Roll the mixture into bite-sized balls. 3. Place on a parchment-lined tray and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes to firm up. 4. Store in an airtight container in the fridge for up to a week.

Description: Savory cakes with a blend of carrots and zucchini, slightly crispy on the outside and soft inside, perfect as a light dinner.
Ingredients: 1 cup grated carrots, 1 cup grated zucchini, � cup whole wheat flour, 1 egg, 1 teaspoon garlic powder, 1 teaspoon onion powder, Salt and pepper to taste, Olive oil for frying
Instructions: 1. In a bowl, mix grated carrots, zucchini, flour, egg, garlic powder, onion powder, salt, and pepper until combined. 2. Heat a skillet over medium heat with olive oil. 3. Drop spoonfuls of the mixture onto the skillet and flatten slightly. 4. Cook for about 4-5 minutes on each side until golden brown. 5. Serve warm.

Description: A delicious twist on classic oats combining the flavors of carrot cake with healthy ingredients for breakfast.
Ingredients: 1 cup rolled oats, 1 cup almond milk, � cup grated carrots, 1 tablespoon chia seeds, 1 tablespoon maple syrup, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, � teaspoon nutmeg, 2 tablespoons raisins
Instructions: 1. In a jar or bowl, combine oats, almond milk, grated carrots, chia seeds, maple syrup, cinnamon, and nutmeg. 2. Mix well and stir in raisins. 3. Cover and refrigerate overnight. 4. In the morning, stir and enjoy cold or heated.

Description: A refreshing and colorful dish that combines fresh fish with citrus and tropical flavors, perfect for a light dinner or appetizer.
Ingredients: 1 lb firm white fish (like cod or tilapia), diced. 1 cup fresh lime juice. 1 ripe avocado, diced. 1 cup diced mango. 1 medium red onion, finely chopped. 1 jalape�o, deseeded and minced. � cup fresh cilantro, chopped. Salt to taste.
Instructions: 1. In a glass bowl, combine the diced fish and lime juice. Ensure the fish is completely submerged. Let it marinate for 30 minutes until the fish is opaque. 2. Drain some of the lime juice, leaving enough to coat the fish. 3. Gently mix in the avocado, mango, onion, jalape�o, cilantro, and salt. 4. Serve immediately in small bowls or chilled on a plate.

Recipe Name: Ceviche with Cucumber and Cherry Tomatoes
Description: A light and zesty option filled with fresh produce, perfect for a warm day.
Ingredients: 1 lb shrimp, peeled and deveined. 1 cup fresh lime juice. 1 medium cucumber, diced. 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved. 1 small red onion, finely chopped. � cup fresh cilantro, chopped. Salt and pepper to taste.
Instructions: 1. In a glass bowl, combine shrimp and lime juice, let it marinate for about 30 minutes until opaque. 2. Drain excess lime juice, then fold in cucumber, cherry tomatoes, onion, cilantro, salt, and pepper. 3. Serve chilled with tortilla chips or on a bed of greens.

Recipe Name: Ceviche with Quinoa and Bell Peppers
Description: A nutritious twist on traditional ceviche, combining proteins from fish and quinoa for a filling meal.
Ingredients: 1 lb firm white fish, diced. 1 cup fresh lime juice. � cup quinoa, rinsed. 1 medium red bell pepper, diced. 1 medium green bell pepper, diced. � cup fresh cilantro, chopped. Salt to taste.
Instructions: 1. Cook quinoa according to package instructions and let cool. 2. Marinate fish in lime juice for 30 minutes until opaque. 3. Drain excess lime juice and add cooled quinoa, bell peppers, cilantro, and salt. Mix gently. 4. Serve chilled or at room temperature.

Description: A tropical take on ceviche that balances sweet and tangy flavors, ideal for summer gatherings.
Ingredients: 1 lb firm white fish or shrimp, diced. 1 cup fresh lime juice. 1 cup pineapple, diced. � cup fresh cilantro, chopped. 1 medium red onion, finely chopped. 1 jalape�o, minced. Salt to taste.
Instructions: 1. Marinate the fish or shrimp in lime juice for about 30 minutes until opaque. 2. Drain excess lime juice and fold in pineapple, cilantro, onion, jalape�o, and salt. 3. Serve in small cups or on tostadas for a festive presentation.

Description: A tangy and crunchy alternative to traditional ceviche, with a refreshing twist from radishes.
Ingredients: 1 lb scallops, diced. 1 cup fresh lime juice. 1 cup radishes, thinly sliced. 1 medium cucumber, diced. � cup fresh cilantro, chopped. Salt and pepper to taste.
Instructions: 1. Combine scallops with lime juice in a glass bowl, let marinate for 30 minutes until they are opaque. 2. Add sliced radishes, cucumber, cilantro, salt, and pepper, mixing gently. 3. Serve immediately for the best texture and flavor.

Description: A flavorful, creamy snack that's perfect for gatherings or as a savory appetizer.
Ingredients: 1 cup low-fat cream cheese, softened. 1 cup shredded low-fat cheddar cheese. � cup grated Parmesan cheese. 2 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped. 2 tablespoons fresh chives, chopped. � teaspoon garlic powder. � teaspoon onion powder. Salt and pepper to taste.
Instructions: 1. In a mixing bowl, combine the cream cheese, cheddar cheese, and Parmesan cheese. 2. Add the chopped parsley, chives, garlic powder, onion powder, salt, and pepper. Mix until well combined. 3. Using your hands, form the mixture into small balls, about 1 inch in diameter. 4. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes before serving to firm up. 5. Serve chilled or at room temperature.

Description: A simple yet delightful cheese ball made to please any crowd.
Ingredients: 8 oz low-fat cream cheese, softened. 1 cup shredded mozzarella cheese. � cup chopped fresh herbs (parsley, dill). 1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce. � teaspoon black pepper. � teaspoon paprika.
Instructions: 1. In a medium bowl, use a hand mixer to blend the cream cheese until smooth. 2. Stir in mozzarella cheese, herbs, Worcestershire sauce, black pepper, and paprika. Mix until all ingredients are well combined. 3. Form the mixture into a round ball (or two smaller balls if preferred). 4. Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 1 hour to set. 5. Serve with low-sodium crackers or vegetable sticks.

Description: These healthy cheese balls packed with spinach make for a tasty and nutritious snack.
Ingredients: 1 cup low-fat cottage cheese. 1 cup fresh spinach, finely chopped. 1 cup shredded part-skim mozzarella cheese. 2 tablespoons nutritional yeast. � teaspoon garlic powder. Salt and pepper to taste.
Instructions: 1. Preheat oven to 350�F (175�C) and line a baking sheet with parchment paper. 2. In a mixing bowl, combine cottage cheese, chopped spinach, mozzarella cheese, nutritional yeast, garlic powder, salt, and pepper. 3. Mix until well incorporated. 4. Shape the mixture into small balls and place on the prepared baking sheet. 5. Bake for 20-25 minutes, or until the balls are heated through and slightly golden. Serve warm.

Description: A creamy, guilt-free snack that combines avocado with cheese for a tasty treat.
Ingredients: 2 ripe avocados, mashed. 1 cup low-fat cream cheese, softened. � cup shredded low-fat cheddar cheese. 1 tablespoon lime juice. Salt and pepper to taste.
Instructions: 1. In a mixing bowl, combine the mashed avocados, cream cheese, cheddar cheese, lime juice, salt, and pepper. Mix until smooth and creamy. 2. Form into balls using your hands (about 1-inch diameter). 3. Place the balls onto a tray and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes to chill. 4. Serve with whole grain crackers or fresh vegetables.

Description: A tangy and herby snack option that's great for any occasion.
Ingredients: 1 cup crumbled feta cheese. � cup low-fat cream cheese, softened. � cup fresh dill, chopped. 2 tablespoons lemon juice. Salt and pepper to taste.
Instructions: 1. In a bowl, combine crumbled feta cheese and cream cheese. Mix until smooth. 2. Add chopped dill, lemon juice, salt, and pepper. Stir until well combined. 3. Form into small balls and place on a plate. 4. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour to chill and firm up. 5. Enjoy as a spread on whole-grain bread or with vegetables.

Description: A creamy and delicious cheese fondue that's perfect for sharing, using low-sodium cheese and broth for a renal-friendly option.
Ingredients: 2 cups low-sodium vegetable broth. 8 oz low-sodium Swiss cheese, shredded. 4 oz low-sodium cheddar cheese, shredded. 2 tablespoons cornstarch. 1 tablespoon lemon juice. 1 clove garlic, minced. Fresh vegetables (carrots, broccoli, bell peppers, etc.) for dipping.
Instructions: 1. In a saucepan, gently heat the low-sodium vegetable broth and minced garlic over medium heat until warm. 2. In a bowl, toss the shredded cheeses with cornstarch until evenly coated. 3. Gradually add the cheese mixture to the warm broth, stirring constantly until melted and smooth. 4. Stir in lemon juice and adjust consistency with more broth if needed. Serve warm with fresh vegetables for dipping.

Description: A delightful blend of cheeses with herbs, creating a savory melt that is perfect for a cozy gathering.
Ingredients: 1 cup low-sodium vegetable broth. 6 oz low-sodium mozzarella cheese, shredded. 2 oz low-sodium cream cheese. 1 tablespoon fresh thyme, chopped. 1 tablespoon fresh basil, chopped. 1 clove garlic, minced. Sliced zucchini and bell peppers for dipping.
Instructions: 1. Heat the low-sodium vegetable broth and minced garlic in a saucepan over medium heat. 2. In a bowl, mix together mozzarella and cream cheese. 3. Gradually add cheese to the broth, stirring until melted and creamy. 4. Stir in fresh herbs and serve with sliced vegetables for dipping.

Description: A zesty cheese fondue with a kick, adapted for a renal-friendly diet.
Ingredients: 1 cup low-sodium vegetable broth. 8 oz low-sodium pepper jack cheese, shredded. 2 oz low-sodium cream cheese. 1 tablespoon jalape�o, diced (optional). 1 clove garlic, minced. Fresh cut veggies (carrots, celery) for dipping.
Instructions: 1. In a pot, warm the low-sodium vegetable broth and minced garlic over medium heat. 2. In a mixing bowl, combine the shredded pepper jack and cream cheese. 3. Slowly whisk the cheese mixture into the broth until smooth. 4. Stir in jalape�o if desired, and serve with fresh veggies.

Description: A savory, earthy cheese fondue enhanced with mushrooms for extra flavor without compromising a renal diet.
Ingredients: 1 cup low-sodium vegetable broth. 6 oz low-sodium gouda cheese, shredded. 2 oz low-sodium cream cheese. 1 cup mushrooms, finely chopped. 1 clove garlic, minced.
Instructions: 1. Saut� the chopped mushrooms and garlic in a saucepan until soft. 2. Add low-sodium vegetable broth and warm over medium heat. 3. Stir in gouda and cream cheese gradually, melting until creamy. 4. Serve with whole-grain bread or low-sodium crackers for dipping.

Description: A fragrant and creamy cheese fondue infused with garlic and herbs, great for a cozy night.
Ingredients: 1 cup low-sodium vegetable broth. 7 oz low-sodium Havarti cheese, shredded. 3 oz low-sodium cream cheese. 1 teaspoon garlic powder. 1 tablespoon fresh parsley, chopped. Fresh bread cubes for dipping.
Instructions: 1. Warm the low-sodium vegetable broth in a pot over medium heat. 2. In a bowl, combine Havarti and cream cheese. 3. Gradually add cheese mixture to the broth, stirring continuously until melted. 4. Mix in garlic powder and parsley. Serve with bread cubes for dipping.

Description: A creamy cheesecake with a wholesome almond crust that's lower in sugar and renal-friendly.
Ingredients: 1 � cups almond flour, 2 tablespoons granulated erythritol, � cup unsalted butter, melted, 16 oz cream cheese, softened, � cup granulated erythritol, 3 large eggs, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract, � cup sour cream
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 350�F (175�C). 2. In a bowl, mix the almond flour, erythritol, and melted butter until well combined. 3. Press the mixture into the bottom of a 9-inch springform pan to form the crust. 4. Bake for 10-12 minutes or until lightly golden. 5. In another bowl, beat the cream cheese and erythritol until smooth. Add the eggs, one at a time, blending well after each addition. 6. Stir in the vanilla and sour cream until just combined. 7. Pour the filling over the cooled crust and smooth the top. 8. Bake for another 50-60 minutes, or until the center is set but still slightly jiggly. 9. Let cool and refrigerate for at least 4 hours before serving.

Description: A light and fluffy mousse cheesecake that's bursting with berry flavors and is easy to prepare.
Ingredients: 1 cup low-fat cream cheese, � cup plain Greek yogurt, � cup mixed berries, pureed, 3 tablespoons granulated erythritol, 2 teaspoons gelatin dissolved in 2 tablespoons warm water
Instructions: 1. In a mixing bowl, combine cream cheese and erythritol, and beat until smooth. 2. Add the Greek yogurt and mix until well incorporated. 3. Stir in the pureed berries and gelatin mixture until fully combined. 4. Spoon into serving dishes and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.

Description: A light and refreshing lemon-flavored cheesecake made with ricotta cheese, perfect for a summer dessert.
Ingredients: 1 � cups ricotta cheese, � cup granulated erythritol, 3 large eggs, 2 tablespoons lemon zest, 2 tablespoons lemon juice, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 325�F (160�C). 2. In a mixing bowl, combine ricotta cheese and erythritol until smooth. 3. Add the eggs one at a time, then stir in the lemon zest, lemon juice, and vanilla. 4. Pour the mixture into a greased 9-inch springform pan. 5. Bake for 45-50 minutes or until set and lightly golden on top. 6. Let cool, then refrigerate for at least 3 hours before serving.

Description: An indulgent yet healthy cheesecake made with ripe avocados and dark chocolate, rich in flavor and nutrition.
Ingredients: 2 ripe avocados, � cup unsweetened cocoa powder, � cup granulated erythritol, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract, � cup unsweetened almond milk
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 350�F (175�C). 2. In a bowl, blend the avocados until creamy. 3. Add cocoa powder, erythritol, vanilla extract, and almond milk and blend until fully smooth and combined. 4. Pour into a greased springform pan and smooth the top. 5. Bake for 25-30 minutes. 6. Let cool and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.

Description: A seasonal delight combining pumpkin puree with traditional cheesecake flavors for a wholesome dessert.
Ingredients: 1 � cups cream cheese, 1 cup pumpkin puree, � cup granulated erythritol, 3 large eggs, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, � teaspoon nutmeg
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 350�F (175�C). 2. In a bowl, blend cream cheese and erythritol until smooth. 3. Add the pumpkin puree, eggs, cinnamon, and nutmeg. Mix until just combined. 4. Pour into a greased springform pan and smooth the top. 5. Bake for 50 minutes or until set. 6. Let cool, then refrigerate for at least 4 hours before serving.

Description: A classic dessert, this cherry pie features a flaky crust filled with a sweet and tangy cherry filling, perfect for satisfying your sweet tooth.
Ingredients: 2 cups fresh or frozen cherries, pitted. � cup sugar. 2 tablespoons cornstarch. 1 tablespoon lemon juice. 1 teaspoon vanilla extract. 1 tablespoon butter, diced. 1 pre-made pie crust.
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 425�F (220�C). 2. In a medium bowl, combine cherries, sugar, cornstarch, lemon juice, and vanilla extract. Mix well and set aside for 10 minutes. 3. Roll out the pie crust and place it in a pie dish. Pour the cherry mixture into the crust and dot with butter. 4. Cover with a second pie crust, sealing the edges and making slits for ventilation. 5. Bake for 30-35 minutes or until golden brown. Let cool before serving.

Description: A rustic and inviting dessert, this galette has a crisp almond crust with a juicy cherry filling, offering a delightful flavor combination.
Ingredients: 2 cups fresh or frozen cherries, pitted. 1/3 cup sugar. 1 tablespoon cornstarch. 1 teaspoon almond extract. 1 pre-made pie crust. 2 tablespoons sliced almonds.
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 400�F (200�C). 2. In a bowl, mix cherries, sugar, cornstarch, and almond extract. Set aside. 3. Roll out the pie crust on parchment paper. Place the cherry mixture in the center, leaving an edge. Fold the edges of the crust over the filling. 4. Sprinkle sliced almonds on top. 5. Bake for 25-30 minutes until the crust is golden. Cool before slicing.

Description: These chewy bars combine oats and cherries for a healthy and satisfying snack or dessert, rich in flavors and nutrients.
Ingredients: 1 � cups oats. � cup almond flour. � cup honey. 1 cup fresh or frozen cherries, pitted and chopped. 1 tablespoon chia seeds.
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 350�F (175�C) and line a baking dish with parchment paper. 2. In a large bowl, combine oats, almond flour, and chia seeds. 3. Mix in honey until well combined. 4. Fold in chopped cherries. 5. Press the mixture into the prepared baking dish evenly. Bake for 20-25 minutes until set. Let cool before cutting into bars.

Description: A refreshing and nutritious smoothie packed with cherries, bananas, and yogurt, perfect for a quick breakfast or snack.
Ingredients: 1 cup fresh or frozen cherries, pitted. 1 banana. 1 cup low-fat yogurt. � cup almond milk. 1 tablespoon honey (optional).
Instructions: 1. In a blender, combine cherries, banana, yogurt, almond milk, and honey. 2. Blend until smooth. 3. Pour into glasses and serve immediately.

Description: A delicious and healthy pudding made with chia seeds and cherries, offering a great source of fiber and antioxidants.
Ingredients: � cup chia seeds. 2 cups almond milk. 1 cup fresh or frozen cherries, pitted. 2 tablespoons maple syrup.
Instructions: 1. In a bowl, mix chia seeds and almond milk. Stir well to avoid clumps. 2. Add maple syrup and mix again. 3. Let it sit for 15 minutes, then stir again. 4. In serving glasses, layer chia pudding with cherries. 5. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.

Description: A classic Southern dessert with a creamy filling, modified to be friendlier for renal diets.
Ingredients: 1 cup sugar substitute, 3 large eggs, 1 cup almond milk, 1 cup cornmeal, 1 tsp vanilla extract, � cup unsalted butter, melted, 1 tbsp lemon juice, Pinch of salt
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 350�F (175�C). 2. In a mixing bowl, whisk together the sugar substitute and eggs until well combined. 3. Add the almond milk, melted butter, vanilla extract, lemon juice, cornmeal, and salt. Whisk until smooth. 4. Pour the mixture into a greased pie dish. 5. Bake for 30-35 minutes or until the center is set and slightly golden. 6. Let cool before serving.

Description: A tropical twist on the traditional chess pie that�s light and satisfying.
Ingredients: 1 cup sugar substitute, 3 large eggs, 1 cup coconut milk, 1 cup shredded unsweetened coconut, � cup unsalted butter, melted, 1 tsp vanilla extract, 1 tbsp lime juice, Pinch of salt
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 350�F (175�C). 2. In a mixing bowl, whisk together the sugar substitute and eggs until smooth. 3. Stir in the coconut milk, melted butter, vanilla extract, lime juice, shredded coconut, and salt. Mix until well combined. 4. Pour the filling into a greased pie dish. 5. Bake for 30-35 minutes until the filling is set and lightly browned. 6. Cool completely before enjoying.

Description: Decadent and rich, this chocolate chess pie satisfies sweet cravings while being renal-friendly.
Ingredients: 1 cup sugar substitute, 3 large eggs, 1 cup almond milk, � cup unsweetened cocoa powder, � cup unsalted butter, melted, � cup cornmeal, 1 tsp vanilla extract, Pinch of salt
Instructions: 1. Preheat your oven to 350�F (175�C). 2. In a bowl, whisk together the sugar substitute and eggs until well blended. 3. Mix in the almond milk and melted butter. 4. Add the cocoa powder, cornmeal, vanilla extract, and salt. Whisk until fully incorporated. 5. Pour the mixture into a prepared pie dish and bake for 30-35 minutes until set. 6. Allow to cool before slicing.

Description: Combining the flavors of pumpkin and traditional chess pie in a healthier way.
Ingredients: 1 cup sugar substitute, 3 large eggs, 1 cup pumpkin puree, 1 cup almond milk, � cup unsalted butter, melted, � cup cornmeal, 1 tsp pumpkin spice, Pinch of salt
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 350�F (175�C). 2. Whisk together the sugar substitute and eggs until smooth. 3. Stir in the pumpkin puree, almond milk, melted butter, cornmeal, pumpkin spice, and salt. Mix until combined. 4. Pour into a greased pie dish. 5. Bake for 30-35 minutes until filling is set. 6. Cool completely before serving.

Description: A zesty lemon-flavored pie that brightens up the dessert table while being renal-friendly.
Ingredients: 1 cup sugar substitute, 3 large eggs, 1 cup almond milk, � cup unsalted butter, melted, � cup cornmeal, 1/3 cup lemon juice, 1 tsp lemon zest, Pinch of salt
Instructions: 1. Preheat your oven to 350�F (175�C). 2. In a bowl, whisk together the sugar substitute and eggs until well mixed. 3. Add the almond milk and melted butter, whisking to combine. 4. Stir in the cornmeal, lemon juice, lemon zest, and salt until uniform. 5. Pour into a greased pie dish and bake for 30-35 minutes until firm. 6. Let cool before slicing.

Recipe Name: Chicken Adobo with Low Sodium Marinade
Description: A flavorful, tangy Filipino dish that features chicken marinated in vinegar, soy sauce, and spices, perfect for a comforting dinner.
Ingredients: 1 lb chicken thighs, skinless. � cup low-sodium soy sauce. � cup vinegar. 4 cloves garlic, minced. 1 bay leaf. 1 teaspoon peppercorns. 2 tablespoons canola oil. 1 cup water. 1 medium onion, sliced. 1 teaspoon brown sugar
Instructions: 1. In a bowl, mix together low-sodium soy sauce, vinegar, garlic, bay leaf, and peppercorns. 2. Marinate the chicken in this mixture for at least 30 minutes. 3. Heat canola oil in a large pot over medium heat. Saut� the onions until translucent. 4. Add the marinated chicken (reserve the marinade) and brown on all sides. 5. Pour in the reserved marinade and water, bringing to a boil. 6. Reduce heat and simmer for about 30-40 minutes or until chicken is tender. 7. Stir in brown sugar, adjust seasoning if needed, and serve hot.

Description: A nutritious twist on traditional chicken adobo, incorporating an array of colorful vegetables for added vitamins and minerals.
Ingredients: 1 lb chicken breasts, skinless. � cup low-sodium soy sauce. � cup vinegar. 4 cloves garlic, minced. 1 bay leaf. 1 teaspoon peppercorns. 1 tablespoon olive oil. 1 cup broccoli florets. 1 bell pepper, sliced. 1 medium carrot, sliced. 1 cup water
Instructions: 1. In a bowl, combine low-sodium soy sauce, vinegar, garlic, bay leaf, and peppercorns. Marinate the chicken for 30 minutes. 2. Heat olive oil in a pan over medium heat. Briefly saut� the chicken until browned. 3. Add the marinated mixture and water, bring to a boil. 4. Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes. 5. Add in the broccoli, bell pepper, and carrot. Cook until vegetables are tender and chicken is fully cooked. Serve warm.

Description: A comforting, slow-cooked version of the classic dish, allowing all flavors to meld together beautifully.
Ingredients: 1 lb chicken thighs, skinless. � cup low-sodium soy sauce. � cup vinegar. 5 cloves garlic, minced. 1 bay leaf. 1 teaspoon black pepper, crushed. 1 cup water
Instructions: 1. Place chicken in a slow cooker. In a bowl, whisk together low-sodium soy sauce, vinegar, garlic, bay leaf, and pepper. Pour over the chicken. 2. Add water and mix well. 3. Cover and cook on low for 6-8 hours or until chicken is tender. 4. Serve with a side of steamed vegetables. Enjoy every bite!

Description: A fun and flavorful way to enjoy chicken adobo, perfect for summer grilling with a hint of smokiness.
Ingredients: 1 lb chicken breasts, skinless, cut into cubes. � cup low-sodium soy sauce. � cup vinegar. 3 cloves garlic, minced. 1 tablespoon olive oil. 1 teaspoon oregano. 1 tablespoon honey
Instructions: 1. In a bowl, mix soy sauce, vinegar, garlic, olive oil, oregano, and honey. Marinate chicken cubes for 30 minutes. 2. Preheat grill to medium-high heat. Thread marinated chicken onto skewers. 3. Grill skewers for 10-15 minutes, turning occasionally, until chicken is cooked through. Serve with a fresh salad.

Description: A hearty soup version of the classic chicken adobo, filled with vegetables and warming spices for a soothing meal.
Ingredients: 1 lb chicken thighs, skinless. � cup low-sodium soy sauce. � cup vinegar. 5 cloves garlic, minced. 1 bay leaf. 1 teaspoon black pepper, crushed. 4 cups low-sodium chicken broth. 1 cup diced potatoes. 1 cup chopped kale
Instructions: 1. In a large pot, combine chicken, soy sauce, vinegar, garlic, bay leaf, and pepper. 2. Add chicken broth and bring to a boil. 3. Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes. 4. Add diced potatoes and cook until tender. 5. Stir in chopped kale and simmer for an additional 5 minutes. Serve warm.

Recipe Name: Chicken and Dumplings with Low-Sodium Broth
Description: A comforting dish featuring tender chicken and fluffy dumplings perfect for a hearty dinner.
Ingredients: 2 cups low-sodium chicken broth, 1 pound boneless, skinless chicken breast, diced, 1 cup carrots, diced, 1 cup celery, diced, 1 medium onion, chopped, 1 cup all-purpose flour, 2 teaspoons baking powder, � teaspoon salt, 1 cup skim milk, 2 tablespoons olive oil, 1 teaspoon dried thyme
Instructions: 1. In a large pot, bring low-sodium chicken broth to a simmer over medium heat. 2. Add diced chicken, carrots, celery, and onion. Cook until chicken is no longer pink and vegetables are tender, about 15 minutes. 3. In a bowl, mix flour, baking powder, and salt. Stir in milk and olive oil until combined. 4. Drop spoonfuls of the dough into the simmering broth. Cover and cook for 15 minutes or until dumplings are cooked through. 5. Stir in dried thyme, adjust seasonings if needed, and serve warm.

Description: A savory one-pot meal featuring chicken, vegetables, and tender dumplings for a delicious family dinner.
Ingredients: 1 pound boneless chicken thighs, diced, 2 cups low-sodium chicken broth, 1 cup carrots, sliced, 1 cup green beans, trimmed, 1 cup peas, 2 cups all-purpose flour, 2 teaspoons baking powder, 1 teaspoon garlic powder, � teaspoon black pepper, 1 � cups skim milk, 2 tablespoons olive oil
Instructions: 1. In a large pot, heat olive oil over medium heat. 2. Add diced chicken and cook until browned. 3. Pour in chicken broth and add carrots, green beans, and peas, simmer for 10 minutes. 4. In a bowl, mix flour, baking powder, garlic powder, and pepper. Stir in milk to form a batter. 5. Drop dumpling batter into the simmering pot. Cover and cook for an additional 15 minutes or until dumplings are fluffy and cooked through. Serve hot.

Recipe Name: Creamy Chicken and Dumplings without Cream
Description: A lighter version of the classic dish with tender chicken and dumplings in a deliciously creamy sauce without the heavy cream.
Ingredients: 1 pound skinless chicken breast, shredded, 2 cups low-sodium chicken broth, 1 cup cauliflower florets, 1 cup carrots, diced, 2 cups all-purpose flour, 2 teaspoons baking powder, 1 teaspoon onion powder, 1 � cups unsweetened almond milk, 2 tablespoons olive oil
Instructions: 1. In a large pot, add shredded chicken, low-sodium chicken broth, cauliflower, and carrots. Simmer until the vegetables are tender. 2. In a separate bowl, mix flour, baking powder, and onion powder. Stir in almond milk and olive oil until combined. 3. Spoon the dumpling mixture into the simmering chicken mixture. Cover and cook for 15 minutes until dumplings rise and are fluffy. 4. Adjust seasoning as needed and serve warm.

Description: A flavorful blend of chicken, fresh herbs, and light dumplings, perfect for a satisfying dinner.
Ingredients: 1 pound boneless chicken breast, diced, 2 cups low-sodium chicken broth, 1 cup carrots, diced, 1 cup potatoes, diced, 2 cups all-purpose flour, 1 tablespoon fresh parsley, 1 tablespoon fresh thyme, 1 teaspoon garlic powder, 1 � cups skim milk
Instructions: 1. In a large pot, bring chicken broth to a simmer. Add diced chicken, carrots, and potatoes. Cook until chicken is cooked through and vegetables are tender. 2. In a bowl, combine flour, parsley, thyme, garlic powder, and milk to make a batter. 3. Drop spoonfuls of the batter into the simmering pot. Cover and cook for 15 minutes or until dumplings are cooked through. 4. Stir gently and serve while hot, garnished with more fresh herbs.

Description: A zesty twist on traditional chicken and dumplings, enhanced with a touch of spice and flavor.
Ingredients: 1 pound boneless chicken thighs, diced, 2 cups low-sodium chicken broth, 1 cup bell peppers, diced, 1 cup corn, 2 cups all-purpose flour, 1 teaspoon chili powder, 1 teaspoon cumin, 1 � cups skim milk, 2 tablespoons olive oil
Instructions: 1. Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add diced chicken and cook until browned. 2. Add chicken broth, bell peppers, and corn bring to a simmer. 3. In a bowl, mix flour, chili powder, cumin, and milk until a batter forms. 4. Drop spoonfuls of the dumpling mixture into the pot. Cover and cook for 15 minutes. 5. Stir gently to combine flavors and serve hot.

Description: A hearty Italian dish featuring chicken simmered with tomatoes, bell peppers, and herbs for a rich flavor.
Ingredients: 4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts. 1 tablespoon olive oil. 1 medium onion, chopped. 2 cloves garlic, minced. 1 medium red bell pepper, sliced. 1 medium green bell pepper, sliced. 1 can (14.5 oz) diced tomatoes. 1 teaspoon dried oregano. 1 teaspoon dried basil. Salt and pepper to taste. Fresh parsley for garnish
Instructions: 1. Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. 2. Add the chopped onion and saut� until translucent, about 5 minutes. 3. Stir in garlic and cook for an additional minute. 4. Add sliced bell peppers and cook until softened, about 5 minutes. 5. Push veggies to the side and add chicken breasts, browning them on both sides. 6. Pour in diced tomatoes, oregano, basil, salt, and pepper. 7. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover, and simmer for 30 minutes until chicken is cooked through. 8. Garnish with fresh parsley and serve.

Description: A low-carb twist on the classic dish using zucchini noodles instead of pasta, keeping it light and flavorful.
Ingredients: 4 boneless, skinless chicken thighs. 2 medium zucchinis, spiralized. 1 tablespoon olive oil. 1 medium onion, diced. 2 cloves garlic, minced. 1 can (14.5 oz) crushed tomatoes. 1 teaspoon dried thyme. 1 teaspoon dried rosemary. Salt and pepper to taste.
Instructions: 1. Heat olive oil in a large pan over medium heat. 2. Add onion and saut� until softened. 3. Stir in garlic and cook for 1 minute. 4. Add chicken thighs and cook until browned on both sides. 5. Pour in crushed tomatoes, thyme, rosemary, salt, and pepper. 6. Simmer for 30 minutes until chicken is tender. 7. In the last 5 minutes, add spiralized zucchini noodles. Toss to combine and serve hot.

Description: A fast and easy version of chicken cacciatore that can be made in under 30 minutes, perfect for busy weeknights.
Ingredients: 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts, cubed. 1 tablespoon olive oil. 1 medium onion, chopped. 1 can (14.5 oz) diced tomatoes. 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning. Salt and pepper to taste.
Instructions: 1. Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. 2. Add onion and cook until translucent. 3. Add cubed chicken and cook until browned. 4. Stir in diced tomatoes, Italian seasoning, salt, and pepper. 5. Reduce heat, cover, and cook for 15 minutes until chicken is cooked through.

Description: A comforting dish that cooks slowly, allowing the flavors to meld beautifully, ideal for meal prep.
Ingredients: 4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts. 1 can (14.5 oz) diced tomatoes. 1 medium onion, diced. 1 green bell pepper, sliced. 1 tablespoon olive oil. 1 teaspoon dried basil. 1 teaspoon dried oregano. Salt and pepper to taste.
Instructions: 1. Heat olive oil in a skillet and brown chicken breasts. 2. In the slow cooker, combine browned chicken, diced tomatoes, onion, bell pepper, basil, oregano, salt, and pepper. 3. Cook on low for 6 hours or high for 3 hours. Serve warm.

Description: This one-pot meal combines chicken, vegetables, and tomatoes for a simple cleanup and delicious flavor.
Ingredients: 4 boneless, skinless chicken thighs. 1 can (14.5 oz) crushed tomatoes. 1 medium onion, chopped. 1 medium bell pepper, sliced. 1 tablespoon olive oil. 1 teaspoon garlic powder. 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning. Salt and pepper to taste.
Instructions: 1. Heat olive oil in a large pot. 2. Add onion and cook until softened. 3. Brown chicken thighs on both sides. 4. Stir in crushed tomatoes, bell pepper, garlic powder, Italian seasoning, salt, and pepper. 5. Cover and simmer for 25-30 minutes until chicken is cooked through.

Recipe Name: Chicken Cordon Bleu with Spinach and Low-Sodium Ham
Description: A healthy twist on the classic dish, featuring chicken breast stuffed with spinach and low-sodium ham, coated with a crispy crust.
Ingredients: 2 chicken breasts, flattened. 4 slices low-sodium ham. 2 cups fresh spinach, chopped. � cup low-fat cheese, shredded. 1 cup whole wheat breadcrumbs. 2 eggs, beaten. 1 tablespoon olive oil. Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 375�F (190�C). 2. In a bowl, mix chopped spinach and cheese. 3. Place a slice of ham on each chicken breast, add the spinach mixture, and roll tightly. 4. Dredge each roll in beaten eggs, then coat with breadcrumbs. 5. Place on a baking sheet, brush with olive oil, and bake for 25-30 minutes or until golden.

Description: A delicious, hearty bake with quinoa, chicken, low-sodium ham, and cheese for a comforting meal.
Ingredients: 1 cup quinoa, uncooked. 2 cups low-sodium chicken broth. 1 cup cooked chicken, shredded. 4 slices low-sodium ham, chopped. 1 cup low-fat cheese, shredded. � teaspoon garlic powder. � teaspoon onion powder. Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 350�F (175�C). 2. Rinse quinoa under cold water and cook with chicken broth for 15 minutes. 3. In a baking dish, combine cooked quinoa, shredded chicken, ham, cheese, and seasonings. 4. Mix well, cover with foil, and bake for 20 minutes. 5. Uncover and bake for an additional 10 minutes until cheese is bubbly.

Recipe Name: Baked Chicken Cordon Bleu with Cauliflower Rice
Description: A low-carb, renal-friendly version of Chicken Cordon Bleu served over cauliflower rice.
Ingredients: 2 chicken breasts, flattened. 4 slices low-sodium ham. 1 cup cauliflower rice. � cup low-fat cheese, shredded. 1 egg, beaten. 1 teaspoon olive oil. Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 375�F (190�C). 2. In a bowl, prepare a layer of ham on each chicken breast, then sprinkle with cheese. 3. Roll the breasts and dip in beaten egg. 4. Heat olive oil in a skillet, sear each roll on all sides, then place in the oven for 20-25 minutes. 5. In the meantime, steam cauliflower rice for 5-7 minutes. Serve rolls over cauliflower rice.

Recipe Name: Stuffed Peppers with Chicken Cordon Bleu Filling
Description: Bell peppers stuffed with a savory mix of chicken, ham, and low-fat cheese for a colorful, nutrient-rich dish.
Ingredients: 4 bell peppers, halved and seeded. 2 cups cooked chicken, shredded. 4 slices low-sodium ham, chopped. 1 cup low-fat cheese, shredded. 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning. Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions: 1. Preheat oven to 375�F (190�C). 2. In a bowl, combine shredded chicken, ham, cheese, Italian seasoning, salt, and pepper. 3. Spoon filling into each pepper half, place on a baking dish. 4. Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes, uncover for the last 10 minutes until peppers are tender. Serve warm.

Description: A fun, portable option featuring chicken and low-sodium ham on skewers, grilled to perfection and served with a dipping sauce.
Ingredients: 1 pound boneless chicken breast, cut into cubes. 6 slices low-sodium ham, cut into strips. 1 cup low-fat cheese, cubed. 2 tablespoons olive oil. Salt and pepper to taste. Wooden skewers.
Instructions: 1. Preheat grill or grill pan over medium-high heat. 2. Thread chicken, ham, and cheese onto skewers alternately. 3. Brush the skewers with olive oil, season with salt and pepper. 4. Grill for 10-12 minutes, turning occasionally until chicken is cooked through. Serve with a side of low-sodium mustard dipping sauce.

Description: A savory and elegant chicken dish cooked in a rich mushroom and Marsala wine sauce, perfect for a hearty dinner.
Ingredients: 4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts. 1 cup flour, for dredging. 1 teaspoon salt. � teaspoon black pepper. 2 tablespoons olive oil. 1 cup sliced mushrooms. � cup Marsala wine. � cup low-sodium chicken broth. 2 tablespoons unsalted butter. Fresh parsley for garnish
Instructions: 1. Season the chicken breasts with salt and pepper, then dredge in flour, shaking off the excess. 2. In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium-high heat. 3. Add the chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, about 6-7 minutes per side. Remove from skillet and set aside. 4. In the same skillet, add sliced mushrooms and saut� until browned. 5. Pour in the Marsala wine and chicken broth, scraping the bottom of the skillet to deglaze. 6. Bring to a simmer and reduce the sauce until slightly thickened. 7. Stir in butter until melted, then return chicken to the skillet, coating it with the sauce. 8. Serve garnished with fresh parsley.

Description: A lighter twist on classic Chicken Marsala, served over cauliflower rice for a lower-carb option.
Ingredients: 4 boneless, skinless chicken thighs. 1 cup flour, for dredging. � teaspoon salt. � teaspoon black pepper. 2 tablespoons olive oil. 1 cup sliced mushrooms. � cup Marsala wine. � cup low-sodium chicken broth. 2 cups cauliflower rice. 1 tablespoon fresh parsley, chopped
Instructions: 1. Season chicken thighs with salt and pepper, and dredge in flour. 2. Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat, add chicken, and cook until browned, about 5-6 minutes each side. Remove from skillet. 3. In the same skillet, add the mushrooms and saut� until soft. 4. Add Marsala wine and chicken broth, simmering to reduce. 5. Cook cauliflower rice in a separate pan according to package instructions. 6. Return chicken to the skillet, coating with the sauce. 7. Serve chicken over cauliflower rice and garnish with parsley.

Description: A healthy and gluten-free twist, using zucchini noodles to soak up the rich Marsala sauce.
Ingredients: 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts. 4 medium zucchini, spiralized. 1 cup flour, for dredging. 1 teaspoon salt. � teaspoon black pepper. 2 tablespoons olive oil. 1 cup sliced mushrooms. � cup Marsala wine. � cup low-sodium chicken broth. 2 tablespoons fresh basil, chopped
Instructions: 1. Dredge the chicken in flour seasoned with salt and pepper. 2. Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat and cook chicken until browned, about 6-7 minutes per side. Set aside. 3. In the same pan, add mushrooms and saut�. 4. Deglaze with Marsala wine and chicken broth, simmering until sauce is reduced. 5. In a separate pan, saut� zucchini noodles for 2-3 minutes until tender. 6. Return chicken to the sauce, then serve over zucchini noodles with garnished basil.

Description: A nutritious version of Chicken Marsala, plated over protein-rich quinoa for a complete meal.
Ingredients: 4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts. 1 cup quinoa, uncooked. 1 � cups water. 1 cup flour, for dredging. 1 teaspoon salt. � teaspoon black pepper. 2 tablespoons olive oil. 1 cup sliced mushrooms. � cup Marsala wine. � cup low-sodium chicken broth
Instructions: 1. Rinse quinoa under cold water and then combine with water in a pot. Bring to a boil, cover, and reduce heat to simmer for 15 minutes until water is absorbed. 2. Season chicken with salt and pepper, dredge in flour, and saut� in olive oil until golden, about 6-7 minutes per side. 3. In the same pan, cook mushrooms until tender, then add Marsala wine and chicken broth, reducing the sauce. 4. Serve chicken over a bed of quinoa and drizzle with the sauce.

Description: Grilled chicken skewers marinated in a savory Marsala sauce, giving a fun twist to traditional Chicken Marsala.
Ingredients: 1 lb boneless, skinless chicken breast, cut into cubes. � cup Marsala wine. � cup low-sodium chicken broth. 1 tablespoon olive oil. 1 teaspoon garlic powder. 1 teaspoon onion powder. Salt and pepper to taste. 1 cup sliced bell peppers (optional)
Instructions: 1. In a bowl, combine Marsala wine, broth, olive oil, garlic powder, onion powder, salt, and pepper. 2. Add chicken and bell peppers, marinating for at least 30 minutes. 3. Preheat grill or grill pan. 4. Thread marinated chicken and peppers onto skewers. 5. Grill skewers for 10-12 minutes, turning occasionally until chicken is cooked through. 6. Serve with extra marinade as a dipping sauce.

Description: A comforting and hearty soup featuring tender chicken, noodles, and a medley of vegetables.
Ingredients: 1 cup cooked, shredded chicken, 4 cups low-sodium chicken broth, 1 cup egg noodles, 1 cup carrots, diced, 1 cup celery, diced, 1 cup onion, diced, 2 cloves garlic, minced, 1 teaspoon dried thyme, Salt and pepper to taste, 1 tablespoon olive oil, 2 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped
Instructions: 1. In a large pot, heat olive oil over medium heat. 2. Add onion, garlic, carrots, and celery. Saut� until vegetables are tender, about 5-7 minutes. 3. Add chicken broth, shredded chicken, thyme, salt, and pepper. Bring to a boil. 4. Add egg noodles and simmer for about 10 minutes or until noodles are tender. 5. Stir in fresh parsley before serving.

Description: A delicious soup with chicken, spinach, and egg noodles, perfect for a light dinner.
Ingredients: 1 cup cooked, shredded chicken, 4 cups low-sodium chicken broth, 1 cup egg noodles, 2 cups fresh spinach, 1 cup carrots, diced, 1 teaspoon garlic powder, Salt and pepper to taste, 1 tablespoon olive oil, � teaspoon dried basil, 2 tablespoons fresh lemon juice
Instructions: 1. Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat. 2. Add carrots and saut� until tender, about 5 minutes. 3. Pour in chicken broth, add shredded chicken, garlic powder, basil, salt, and pepper. Bring to a boil. 4. Add egg noodles and cook according to package instructions. 5. Stir in fresh spinach and lemon juice before serving.

Description: A rich and creamy version of a classic chicken noodle soup, perfect for warming up on a cold day.
Ingredients: 1 cup cooked, shredded chicken, 4 cups low-sodium chicken broth, 1 cup egg noodles, 1 cup carrots, diced, 1 cup celery, diced, 1 cup heavy cream, 1 teaspoon garlic powder, Salt and pepper to taste, 1 tablespoon olive oil, � teaspoon dried thyme
Instructions: 1. In a pot, heat olive oil over medium heat and saut� carrots and celery until soft. 2. Add in chicken broth and bring to a boil. 3. Stir in the egg noodles and cook until tender. 4. Reduce heat and add the shredded chicken, heavy cream, garlic powder, thyme, salt, and pepper. 5. Cook for an additional 5 minutes before serving.

Description: A refreshing soup with a citrus twist, blending the flavors of lemon and herbs.
Ingredients: 1 cup cooked, shredded chicken, 4 cups low-sodium chicken broth, 1 cup egg noodles, 1 cup zucchini, diced, 1 teaspoon lemon zest, 1 tablespoon fresh lemon juice, 1 teaspoon dried oregano, Salt and pepper to taste, 1 tablespoon olive oil
Instructions: 1. Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add zucchini and saut� for 3-4 minutes. 2. Pour in chicken broth and add chicken, lemon zest, oregano, salt, and pepper. Bring to a boil. 3. Add egg noodles and cook until tender. 4. Stir in lemon juice before serving.

Description: A flavorful soup with Italian seasonings, chicken, and vegetables.
Ingredients: 1 cup cooked, shredded chicken, 4 cups low-sodium chicken broth, 1 cup egg noodles, 1 cup diced tomatoes, 1 cup carrots, diced, 1 cup green beans, chopped, 1 tablespoon Italian seasoning, Salt and pepper to taste, 1 tablespoon olive oil
Instructions: 1. In a pot, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add carrots and saut� until soft. 2. Add diced tomatoes, chicken broth, chicken, Italian seasoning, salt, and pepper. Bring to a boil. 3. Add egg noodles and green beans, cooking until noodles are tender. Serve warm.

Description: A classic Italian-American dish featuring breaded chicken breasts topped with marinara sauce and melted cheese, served with a side of vegetables.
Ingredients: 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts. 1 cup whole wheat breadcrumbs. � cup grated Parmesan cheese. 1 cup low-sodium marinara sauce. 1 cup part-skim mozzarella cheese, shredded. 1 tablespoon olive oil. 1 teaspoon dried oregano. 1 teaspoon garlic powder. Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions: 1. Preheat oven to 375�F (190�C). 2. Season the chicken breasts with salt, pepper, oregano, and garlic powder. 3. Coat each chicken breast in breadcrumbs mixed with Parmesan cheese. 4. Heat olive oil in an oven-safe skillet over medium heat. Add chicken and cook for 4-5 minutes on each side until golden brown. 5. Pour marinara sauce over the chicken and sprinkle with mozzarella cheese. 6. Transfer the skillet to the oven and bake for 20 minutes, until the chicken is cooked through and cheese is melted.

Description: A lighter version of Chicken Parmesan served over spiralized zucchini noodles, making it a low-carb meal.
Ingredients: 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts. 1 cup whole wheat breadcrumbs. � cup grated Parmesan cheese. 1 cup low-sodium marinara sauce. 1 cup part-skim mozzarella cheese, shredded. 1 tablespoon olive oil. 2 medium zucchini, spiralized. 1 teaspoon dried basil. Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions: 1. Preheat oven to 375�F (190�C). 2. Season the chicken with salt, pepper, and basil. 3. Coat chicken in breadcrumbs mixed with Parmesan cheese. 4. In a skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat, cook chicken for 4-5 minutes on each side. 5. Pour marinara sauce and top with mozzarella, then bake for 20 minutes. 6. While chicken bakes, saut� spiralized zucchini in a separate pan for 3-4 minutes. 7. Serve chicken on top of zucchini noodles.

Recipe Name: Baked Chicken Parmesan with Spinach Salad
Description: A twist on the traditional dish served alongside a fresh spinach salad, giving a balanced meal.
Ingredients: 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts. 1 cup whole wheat breadcrumbs. � cup grated Parmesan cheese. 1 cup low-sodium marinara sauce. 1 cup part-skim mozzarella cheese, shredded. 1 tablespoon olive oil. 3 cups fresh spinach. 1 tablespoon balsamic vinegar. � teaspoon garlic powder. Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions: 1. Preheat oven to 375�F (190�C). 2. Season chicken with salt, pepper, and garlic powder. Coat in breadcrumbs mixed with Parmesan. 3. Heat olive oil in a skillet, cook chicken until golden on each side. 4. Add marinara and mozzarella on top, then bake for 20 minutes. 5. Toss spinach with balsamic vinegar and season with salt and pepper. 6. Serve chicken alongside spinach salad.

Description: A creative take on Chicken Parmesan, featuring bell peppers filled with seasoned chicken and cheese.
Ingredients: 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts. 4 bell peppers (any color). 1 cup whole wheat breadcrumbs. � cup grated Parmesan cheese. 1 cup low-sodium marinara sauce. 1 cup part-skim mozzarella cheese, shredded. 1 tablespoon olive oil. 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning. Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions: 1. Preheat oven to 375�F (190�C). 2. Cut tops off bell peppers and remove seeds. 3. Season chicken with salt, pepper, and Italian seasoning, cook in olive oil until browned. 4. Combine chicken with breadcrumbs and Parmesan. Stuff peppers with the mixture. 5. Top with marinara and mozzarella, then bake for 25-30 minutes.

Description: A healthy version of Chicken Parmesan that reduces sodium while maintaining flavor.
Ingredients: 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts. 1 cup whole wheat breadcrumbs. � cup grated Parmesan cheese. 1 cup low-sodium marinara sauce. 1 cup part-skim mozzarella cheese, shredded. 1 tablespoon olive oil. 1 teaspoon dried Italian herbs. Black pepper to taste
Instructions: 1. Preheat oven to 375�F (190�C). 2. Season chicken with black pepper and Italian herbs. 3. Coat with breadcrumbs mixed with Parmesan. 4. Saut� chicken in olive oil until golden, then add marinara sauce and mozzarella. 5. Bake for 20 minutes until chicken is done and cheese is bubbly.

Description: A flavorful Italian dish featuring tender chicken breasts in a lemony caper sauce, served with a side of vegetables
Ingredients: 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts, 1/2 cup all-purpose flour, 2 tablespoons olive oil, 2 tablespoons unsalted butter, 1/2 cup low-sodium chicken broth, 1/4 cup fresh lemon juice, 1/4 cup capers, 1 tablespoon fresh parsley, Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions: 1. Season the chicken breasts with salt and pepper on both sides. 2. Dredge each chicken breast in flour, shaking off the excess. 3. In a large skillet, heat olive oil and butter over medium heat until melted. 4. Add the chicken breasts and cook for about 5-7 minutes on each side or until golden brown and cooked through. Remove the chicken and set aside. 5. In the same skillet, add chicken broth, lemon juice, and capers. Bring to a simmer and let it reduce for 2-3 minutes. 6. Return the chicken to the skillet and cook for an additional 2 minutes, spooning the sauce over the chicken. 7. Garnish with fresh parsley and serve.

Description: A lighter version of chicken piccata served over healthy zucchini noodles, perfect for a low-carb meal
Ingredients: 2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts, 1/2 cup almond flour, 2 tablespoons olive oil, 2 tablespoons unsalted butter, 1/2 cup low-sodium chicken broth, 1/4 cup fresh lemon juice, 1/4 cup capers, 2 medium zucchinis, Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions: 1. Spiralize the zucchinis into noodles and set aside. 2. Season the chicken breasts with salt and pepper. 3. Dredge chicken in almond flour. 4. In a skillet, heat olive oil and butter over medium heat. 5. Add chicken and cook for about 5-7 minutes on each side until golden brown. Remove and set aside. 6.
