Description: A nutritious and flavorful waffle made with sweet potatoes, perfect for breakfast or a snack.
Ingredients: 1 cup mashed sweet potatoes, 1 cup whole wheat flour, 1/2 cup almond milk, 1 teaspoon baking powder, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1 tablespoon maple syrup
Instructions: 1. Preheat the waffle iron. 2. In a bowl, combine mashed sweet potatoes, whole wheat flour, almond milk, baking powder, cinnamon, and maple syrup. Mix until smooth. 3. Lightly grease the waffle iron and pour in the batter. Cook until golden brown. 4. Serve warm with toppings of your choice such as yogurt or fresh fruit.

Recipe Name: Waffle with Blueberries and Chia Seeds
Description: A light and fluffy waffle loaded with antioxidants from fresh blueberries and chia seeds, great for breakfast.
Ingredients: 1 cup whole wheat flour, 1 cup almond milk, 1/2 cup fresh blueberries, 2 tablespoons chia seeds, 1 teaspoon baking powder, 1 tablespoon honey
Instructions: 1. Preheat the waffle iron. 2. In a bowl, mix whole wheat flour, almond milk, blueberries, chia seeds, baking powder, and honey until well combined. 3. Lightly grease the waffle iron and pour in the batter. Cook until golden and crisp. 4. Serve warm, optionally topped with additional blueberries.

Recipe Name: Waldorf Salad with Apples and Walnuts
Description: A classic and refreshing salad featuring crisp apples, crunchy walnuts, and a creamy dressing, perfect for a light lunch or side.
Ingredients: 2 medium apples, diced. 1 cup celery, chopped. 1 cup seedless grapes, halved. 1 cup walnuts, chopped. 1/2 cup plain Greek yogurt. 1 tablespoon lemon juice, 1 tablespoon honey, Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions: 1. In a large mixing bowl, combine the diced apples, chopped celery, halved grapes, and chopped walnuts. 2. In a small bowl, whisk together Greek yogurt, lemon juice, honey, salt, and pepper. 3. Pour the dressing over the salad and toss to combine. 4. Serve chilled or at room temperature.

Description: A protein-packed twist on the classic Waldorf salad, featuring tender chicken and a creamy dressing, great for a hearty lunch.
Ingredients: 2 cups cooked chicken breast, shredded. 2 medium apples, diced. 1 cup celery, chopped. 1 cup walnuts, chopped. 1/2 cup Greek yogurt. 1 tablespoon lemon juice, 1 tablespoon honey, Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions: 1. In a large bowl, combine shredded chicken, diced apples, chopped celery, and walnuts. 2. In another bowl, mix Greek yogurt, lemon juice, honey, salt, and pepper until well combined. 3. Pour the dressing over the chicken mixture and toss to coat evenly. 4. Refrigerate for 30 minutes before serving, chilled or at room temperature.

Description: A delicious plant-based version of the Waldorf salad, featuring a variety of fruits and nuts, perfect for a refreshing meal.
Ingredients: 2 medium apples, diced. 1 cup celery, chopped. 1 cup grapes, halved. 1 cup pecans, chopped. 1/2 cup vegan mayonnaise. 1 tablespoon apple cider vinegar, Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions: 1. In a large mixing bowl, combine apples, celery, grapes, and pecans. 2. In a small bowl, whisk together vegan mayonnaise, apple cider vinegar, salt, and pepper. 3. Pour the dressing over the salad mixture and toss to combine. 4. Serve chilled for a refreshing meal.

Description: A delightful variation featuring sweet dried cranberries for added flavor, making it perfect as a side dish.
Ingredients: 2 medium apples, diced. 1 cup celery, chopped. 1 cup grapes, halved. 1/2 cup dried cranberries. 1 cup walnuts, chopped. 1/2 cup plain Greek yogurt. 1 tablespoon lemon juice, Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions: 1. In a large bowl, mix together diced apples, celery, grapes, dried cranberries, and walnuts. 2. In a separate bowl, whisk together Greek yogurt, lemon juice, salt, and pepper. 3. Pour the dressing over the fruit and nut mixture and toss well. 4. Chill for at least 30 minutes before serving.

Description: A hearty and nutritious twist with quinoa for extra protein and fiber, making it a filling option.
Ingredients: 1 cup quinoa, cooked. 2 medium apples, diced. 1 cup celery, chopped. 1 cup walnuts, chopped. 1/2 cup plain Greek yogurt. 1 tablespoon lemon juice, Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions: 1. Cook quinoa according to package instructions and let it cool. 2. In a large bowl, combine cooked quinoa, diced apples, celery, and walnuts. 3. In a separate bowl, whisk together Greek yogurt, lemon juice, salt, and pepper. 4. Stir the dressing into the salad, mixing thoroughly. 5. Serve chilled or at room temperature.

Recipe Name: Whoopie Pies with Low Potassium Cocoa
Description: A delightful dessert combining soft chocolate cookies sandwiching a creamy filling, suitable for a renal diet.
Ingredients: 1 � cups all-purpose flour, � cup unsweetened cocoa powder, 1 cup granulated sugar, 1 teaspoon baking soda, � teaspoon salt, � cup unsalted butter, softened, 1 large egg, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract, � cup milk, 1 cup powdered sugar, 2 tablespoons unsweetened cocoa powder, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract, 2 tablespoons unsalted butter, softened
Instructions: 1. Preheat your oven to 350�F (175�C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. 2. In a bowl, sift together flour, cocoa powder, baking soda, and salt. 3. In a separate bowl, cream together softened butter and granulated sugar until light and fluffy. 4. Beat in the egg and vanilla extract. Gradually add the dry ingredients, alternating with milk, mixing until just combined. 5. Drop tablespoonfuls of batter onto the prepared baking sheet, spacing them about 2 inches apart. 6. Bake for 10-12 minutes, until the tops are springy to the touch. Let cool completely. 7. For the filling, cream together powdered sugar, cocoa powder, vanilla extract, and softened butter until smooth. 8. Spread the filling on the flat side of one cookie and place another cookie on top to form a sandwich.

Description: A delicious take on the classic, featuring peanut butter cookies filled with a sweet creamy mixture, designed for a renal-friendly diet.
Ingredients: 1 cup creamy peanut butter, 1 cup granulated sugar, 2 large eggs, 1 teaspoon baking powder, � teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract, 1 cup powdered sugar, 3 tablespoons milk, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract
Instructions: 1. Preheat your oven to 350�F (175�C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. 2. In a bowl, mix together peanut butter, sugar, eggs, baking powder, salt, and vanilla until well combined. 3. Drop tablespoonfuls onto the prepared baking sheet, spacing them 2 inches apart. 4. Bake for 8-10 minutes until edges are lightly golden. Let cool completely. 5. For the filling, combine powdered sugar, milk, and vanilla extract, mixing until smooth. 6. Spread filling onto the flat side of one cookie and sandwich with another.

Description: A heavenly twist on the traditional whoopie pie, combining almond flour for a unique flavor profile while keeping it renal-friendly.
Ingredients: 1 cup almond flour, � cup all-purpose flour, 1 cup granulated sugar, � teaspoon baking powder, � teaspoon salt, � cup unsalted butter, softened, 2 large eggs, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract, 1 cup powdered sugar, 2 tablespoons almond milk, 1 teaspoon almond extract
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 350�F (175�C), line a baking sheet with parchment paper. 2. In a bowl, mix almond flour, all-purpose flour, baking powder, and salt. 3. In a separate bowl, cream together softened butter and sugar until fluffy. 4. Beat in eggs and vanilla extract. Gradually add the dry mixture until combined. 5. Drop tablespoons onto the baking sheet and bake for 10-12 minutes. Let cool completely. 6. For the filling, beat together powdered sugar, almond milk, and almond extract until smooth. 7. Spread filling between two cookies and serve.

Description: A fall favorite that incorporates pumpkin puree and warm spices, offering a tasty treat on a renal diet.
Ingredients: 1 cup all-purpose flour, � cup pumpkin puree, 1 cup granulated sugar, 1 teaspoon baking powder, 1 teaspoon pumpkin pie spice, � teaspoon salt, 1/3 cup unsalted butter, softened, 1 large egg, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract, 1 cup powdered sugar, 2 tablespoons cream cheese, softened, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract
Instructions: 1. Preheat your oven to 350�F (175�C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. 2. In a bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, pumpkin pie spice, and salt. 3. In another bowl, cream together butter and sugar until fluffy. 4. Add pumpkin puree, egg, and vanilla extract, mixing until combined. Then add dry ingredients until just mixed. 5. Drop tablespoons of batter onto the baking sheet and bake for 10-12 minutes. Let cool. 6. For the filling, beat together powdered sugar, cream cheese, and vanilla until smooth. 7. Spread filling onto cookies and sandwich.

Description: A classic cookie pie with soft chocolate cookies filled with a sweet cream, modified for a renal diet.
Ingredients: 1 cup all-purpose flour, 1 cup chocolate chips, 1 cup granulated sugar, � teaspoon baking soda, � teaspoon salt, � cup unsalted butter, softened, 1 large egg, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract, 1 cup powdered sugar, 2 tablespoons milk
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 350�F (175�C) and line a baking sheet with parchment paper. 2. In a bowl, combine flour, baking soda, and salt. 3. In another bowl, cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy. 4. Add the egg and vanilla extract, and mix. Gradually add the dry mixture, folding in chocolate chips. 5. Drop tablespoonfuls of dough onto the baking sheet and bake for 10-12 minutes. Allow to cool. 6. For the filling, beat together powdered sugar and milk until smooth. 7. Spread filling between two cookies.

Recipe Name: Ziti with Spinach and Low-Sodium Marinara
Description: A comforting dish that pairs whole wheat ziti with nutrient-rich spinach and a low-sodium marinara sauce for a renal-friendly meal.
Ingredients: 2 cups whole wheat ziti, uncooked. 2 cups fresh spinach, chopped. 1 � cups low-sodium marinara sauce. 1 tablespoon olive oil. 1 clove garlic, minced. � teaspoon dried basil. � teaspoon dried oregano. Black pepper to taste.
Instructions: 1. Cook ziti according to package instructions until al dente. Drain and set aside. 2. In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add minced garlic and saut� for about 1 minute until fragrant. 3. Add chopped spinach and cook until wilted, about 3-4 minutes. 4. Stir in the marinara sauce, basil, oregano, and cooked ziti. Mix well and heat through for another 3-5 minutes. 5. Season with black pepper and serve warm.

Recipe Name: Ziti with Grilled Chicken and Bell Peppers
Description: A flavorful dish featuring whole wheat ziti, tender grilled chicken, and bell peppers, perfect for a hearty yet healthy dinner.
Ingredients: 2 cups whole wheat ziti, uncooked. 1 pound boneless, skinless chicken breast. 1 cup bell peppers, sliced. 2 tablespoons olive oil. 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning. Black pepper to taste.
Instructions: 1. Preheat grill to medium-high heat. Season chicken breasts with olive oil, Italian seasoning, and black pepper. 2. Grill chicken for 6-7 minutes on each side until cooked through. Let rest before slicing. 3. Cook ziti according to package instructions until al dente. Drain and set aside. 4. In a skillet, saut� bell peppers in a little olive oil until they are tender. 5. Toss cooked ziti with grilled chicken, saut�ed bell peppers, and any remaining seasoning. Serve warm.

Description: A simple yet satisfying dish where whole wheat ziti is tossed with fresh tomatoes and basil for a light and refreshing meal.
Ingredients: 2 cups whole wheat ziti, uncooked. 2 cups cherry tomatoes, halved. 1 cup fresh basil leaves, chopped. 2 tablespoons olive oil. 1 clove garlic, minced. Salt and black pepper to taste.
Instructions: 1. Cook ziti according to package instructions until al dente. Drain and set aside. 2. In a large bowl, combine cherry tomatoes, minced garlic, and olive oil. Let it sit for 10 minutes to meld flavors. 3. Add cooked ziti and chopped basil to the tomato mixture. Toss to combine and season with salt and black pepper. Serve warm or at room temperature.

Description: A creamy and cheesy dish where whole wheat ziti is combined with steamed broccoli for added nutrition.
Ingredients: 2 cups whole wheat ziti, uncooked. 2 cups broccoli florets, steamed. 1 cup low-fat mozzarella cheese, shredded. 1 cup low-sodium vegetable broth. 1 tablespoon olive oil. Garlic powder to taste.
Instructions: 1. Preheat oven to 350�F (175�C). Cook ziti according to package instructions until al dente. Drain and set aside. 2. In a large mixing bowl, combine cooked ziti, steamed broccoli, vegetable broth, olive oil, and garlic powder. 3. Transfer to a baking dish and top with shredded mozzarella cheese. 4. Bake for 15-20 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly. Serve warm.

Description: A vegetable-packed meal that combines ziti with roasted eggplant and zucchini, bringing flavors of summer to your table.
Ingredients: 2 cups whole wheat ziti, uncooked. 1 cup eggplant, diced. 1 cup zucchini, diced. 2 tablespoons olive oil. 1 cup low-sodium marinara sauce. Italian seasoning to taste.
Instructions: 1. Preheat oven to 400�F (200�C). Toss diced eggplant and zucchini with olive oil and Italian seasoning, then spread on a baking sheet. Roast for about 25 minutes until tender. 2. Cook ziti according to package instructions until al dente. Drain and set aside. 3. In a large bowl, combine roasted vegetables, cooked ziti, and marinara sauce. Mix well. 4. Serve warm, garnished with fresh basil if desired.

Description: A savory zucchini bread that combines the freshness of herbs with the moistness of grated zucchini, perfect for a light lunch or snack.
Ingredients: 2 cups grated zucchini. 1 cup whole wheat flour. 1/2 cup almond flour. 1/4 cup olive oil. 2 large eggs. 1/4 cup unsweetened applesauce. 1 teaspoon baking powder. 1 teaspoon baking soda. 1/2 teaspoon salt. 1 tablespoon fresh dill, chopped. 1 tablespoon fresh parsley, chopped. 1 tablespoon fresh chives, chopped
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 350�F (175�C) and grease a loaf pan. 2. In a large bowl, combine the grated zucchini, olive oil, eggs, and applesauce. Mix well. 3. In another bowl, whisk together the whole wheat flour, almond flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, and herbs. 4. Gradually add the dry ingredients to the zucchini mixture, stirring until just combined. 5. Pour the batter into the prepared loaf pan and bake for 45-50 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean. 6. Allow to cool for 10 minutes before removing from the pan. Slice and serve.

Description: A moist and flavorful zucchini bread made with applesauce, making it a healthier option for snacks or breakfast.
Ingredients: 2 cups grated zucchini. 1 � cups all-purpose flour. 1 cup unsweetened applesauce. 1/2 cup vegetable oil. 2 large eggs. 1 teaspoon baking powder. 1 teaspoon baking soda. 1 teaspoon cinnamon. 1/2 teaspoon salt
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 350�F (175�C) and grease a loaf pan. 2. In a bowl, whisk together the grated zucchini, applesauce, vegetable oil, and eggs until smooth. 3. In a separate bowl, mix the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, and salt. 4. Gradually incorporate the dry ingredients into the wet ingredients, mixing until just combined. 5. Pour the batter into the prepared loaf pan and bake for 50-60 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean. 6. Let it cool before slicing.

Description: These delicious muffins are packed with zucchini, making them a great grab-and-go snack or breakfast.
Ingredients: 1 � cups grated zucchini. 1 � cups whole wheat flour. 1/2 cup honey or maple syrup. 1/4 cup coconut oil, melted. 2 large eggs. 1 teaspoon baking soda. 1 teaspoon cinnamon. 1/2 teaspoon salt
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 350�F (175�C) and line a muffin tin with paper liners. 2. In a bowl, combine the grated zucchini, honey or maple syrup, coconut oil, and eggs. Mix well. 3. In another bowl, whisk together the whole wheat flour, baking soda, cinnamon, and salt. 4. Gradually add the dry mixture to the wet mixture, stirring until combined. 5. Fill the muffin cups 2/3 full and bake for 20-25 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean. 6. Cool on a wire rack before serving.

Description: A delicious zucchini bread infused with cheese, perfect for a savory snack or side for meals.
Ingredients: 2 cups grated zucchini. 1 � cups all-purpose flour. 1 cup shredded low-fat cheese. 1/4 cup olive oil. 2 large eggs. 1 teaspoon baking powder. 1 teaspoon baking soda. 1/2 teaspoon salt
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 350�F (175�C) and grease a loaf pan. 2. In a large bowl, mix together the grated zucchini, olive oil, cheese, and eggs. 3. In another bowl, mix the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. 4. Gradually stir the dry ingredients into the zucchini mixture until just combined. 5. Pour into the prepared loaf pan and bake for 45-50 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean. 6. Let cool before slicing.

Description: A delightful blend of zucchini and walnuts provides a nutty flavor and a healthy option for breakfast or snacks.
Ingredients: 2 cups grated zucchini. 1 � cups whole wheat flour. 1/2 cup chopped walnuts. 1/4 cup honey. 1/4 cup vegetable oil. 2 large eggs. 1 teaspoon baking powder. 1 teaspoon cinnamon. 1/2 teaspoon salt
Instructions: 1. Preheat the oven to 350�F (175�C) and grease a loaf pan. 2. In a bowl, mix the grated zucchini, honey, vegetable oil, and eggs. 3. In another bowl, combine the flour, walnuts, baking powder, cinnamon, and salt. 4. Slowly add the dry ingredients to the zucchini mixture, stirring until just combined. 5. Pour the batter into the pan and bake for 50-60 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean. 6. Allow to cool before slicing.
